# === REBASE NOTES (for AI agents maintaining this patch) ===
# Upstream: https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent/pull/17328
# Rebased against: v2026.5.7 (commit 498bfc7bc, tag v2026.5.7)
# Applied in: /home/xieby1/.config/nixpkgs/usr/cli/ai/hermes/default.nix
#
# ── Conflicts resolved during rebase ──
#
# 1. tools/skill_manager_tool.py
#    - Import: added `List` to typing imports (current code also has
#      `is_truthy_value` which the original patch didn't expect).
#    - skill_manage signature: added `scope` param while keeping
#      `absorbed_into` param (added upstream after original PR).
#    - _delete_skill cleanup: changed `parent != skills_root` to
#      `.resolve()` comparison (project-local roots need absolute path
#      comparison across filesystem boundaries).
#    - Registry call: added `scope=args.get("scope", "global")`.
#
# 2. tools/skills_tool.py
#    - skill_view was completely refactored upstream (commit 59da8ec4e)
#      from first-match-wins to collision-detection.  Adapted the
#      get_all_skills_dirs() change to work with the new collision-
#      detection loop.  The all_dirs building and trusted-dir security
#      check were both updated.
#
# ── Local additions beyond original PR ──
#
# 3. agent/skill_utils.py — _resolve_cwd:
#    Original PR trusted TERMINAL_CWD / HERMES_CWD env vars
#    unconditionally.  Added git-repo gating: env-var CWD is only
#    accepted when it (or a parent) contains a .git directory.
#    Otherwise os.getcwd() wins.  This prevents stale env vars from
#    a previous terminal-tool session from shadowing the real CWD.
#
# 4. agent/skill_utils.py — get_project_skills_dirs:
#    Added `.agents/skills` discovery directory (in addition to the
#    original `.hermes/skills` and `.ai/skills`).  Precedence order:
#    .agents/skills > .hermes/skills > .ai/skills.
#
# ── Future rebase guidance ──
# When this patch fails to apply against a newer hermes version:
# - Check tools/skills_tool.py first — the skill_view collision-
#   detection loop (commit 59da8ec4e) is the most volatile area.
# - The skill_manage tool signature tends to gain params over time;
#   insert `scope` after `absorbed_into` in both the function sig
#   and the registry lambda call.
# - The _resolve_cwd git-repo gating can be dropped if upstream
#   adopts a similar fix.  The .agents/skills path should be kept
#   unless upstream adds it too.

